OL,3,CSwinney told to 'make amends' to Covid
OL,4,Cbereaved if he becomes first minister
OL,6,F"Lives and livelihoods hinged on the
OL,7,Fdecisions that John Swinney
OL,8,Facknowledged were happening "at an
OL,9,Fabsolutely ferocious pace". To erase
OL,10,Fthe discussion that underpinned them
OL,11,Fsmacks of a government that had little
OL,12,Fcare for accountability and was
OL,13,Fcovering its tracks.
OL,15,F"If John Swinney does become the next
OL,16,Ffirst minister, he must explain to the
OL,17,FCovid inquiries and to families how he
OL,18,Fwill overhaul government transparency
OL,19,Fand record keeping to finally end the
OL,20,Fculture of secrecy that has existed
OL,21,Ffor 17 years."
